Introduction to Package Management
=================================

==> When we install applications in windows, we use .exe files. In Linux software is installed through packages. Package management helps us to install , update, remove and manage software efficiently.

Package : Collection of software files

Package Manager :  Tools used to manage packages.

In Redhat based systems
     RPM --> Redhat Package Manager
     YUM --> Yellowdog Updater Modified


how to install the packages?
========================

In windows next-->next-->next -->instrall -->finish

In Linux --> Through rpm and yum commands [ rpm -ivh packagename & yum install packagename]

In Mac  --> Through brew command [ brew install package-name]

In Ubuntu --> Through apt or apt-get command [ apt install package-name]

